# CI/CD for a Containerized Application using Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)

![Azure](https://img.shields.io/badge/Azure-AKS-blue)
![Docker](https://img.shields.io/badge/Docker-Containerized-blue)
![Kubernetes](https://img.shields.io/badge/Kubernetes-Orchestration-326CE5)
![Azure DevOps](https://img.shields.io/badge/Azure%20DevOps-CI%2FCD-blueviolet)

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates a complete DevOps workflow using Azure services. A modern web application is containerized with Docker, stored in Azure Container Registry (ACR), and automatically deployed to Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) through Azure DevOps CI/CD pipelines.

The solution includes monitoring and observability using Azure Monitor and Prometheus.

---

## Architecture Diagram

![Architecture](screenshots/architecture.png)

### Workflow

1. Developer pushes code to Azure Repos
2. Azure DevOps Pipeline triggers automatically
3. Docker image is built
4. Image is pushed to Azure Container Registry (ACR)
5. Kubernetes manifests are applied to AKS
6. Application is exposed using a LoadBalancer Service
7. Azure Monitor and Prometheus collect metrics

---

## Technologies Used

| Technology               | Purpose                 |
| ------------------------ | ----------------------- |
| Azure DevOps             | CI/CD Pipeline          |
| Docker                   | Containerization        |
| Azure Container Registry | Image Repository        |
| Azure Kubernetes Service | Container Orchestration |
| Kubernetes               | Deployment Management   |
| Azure Monitor            | Monitoring              |
| Prometheus               | Metrics Collection      |
| HTML/CSS/JavaScript      | Frontend Application    |

